li.p:
Design and integration of new methods and tools for mathematical program specification, certification, security, and guarantees
on numerical results. Some main ingredients here are: the interleaving of formal proofs, computer arithmetic and computer algebra;
error analysis and computation of certified error bounds;
the study of the relationship between performance and numerical quality; and on the cryptology aspects, focus on the practicality of existing protocols and design of more powerful lattice-based primitives.

